{
  "texts": [
    "14 We see no reason to think that the effects of algorithmic recommendation on attentional moral skill should be any different.",
    "As Vallor points out, \"moral skills appear just as vulnerable to disruption or devaluation by technology-driven shifts in human practices as are professional or artisanal skills such as machining, 14 Relatedly, see Zerilli et al. (2019) on the \"control problem\" posed by AI systems.",
    "interpreting them which give users straightforward, veridical reasons for their outputs (Rudin et al., 2022).",
    "But this is as yet an unfulfilled promise.",
    "Footnote 13 (continued) shoemaking, or gardening\" (2015, p. 109)."
  ]
}